<div class="row featurette">
<div class="col-md-7">
<h3 class="pt-4 pb-3">For students with a Bachelor’s degree in the areas of Life Sciences, Physical Sciences, Mathematics, Statistics and Informatics, or Environmental Sciences&nbsp;</h3>

<p>Students have completed their Bachelor's degree in one or more areas of Life Sciences, Physical Sciences, Mathematics, Statistics and Informatics, or Environmental Sciences can apply for the Master's Degree in Green Data Science. This training is open for Bachelor’s Degrees students in the areas of Agronomy, Forestry, Food Science, Biology, Environment, Landscape Architecture, and sciences in related areas. Priority will be given to candidates with at least one year of professional experience. No prior training in computer science is required.</p>

<p>The Green Data Science master’s program has 30 vacancies available annually.</p>

<h3 class="pt-4 pb-3">Admission requirements</h3>

<ul>
	<li>Hold a bachelor's degree, or legal equivalent, obtained at ISA or other higher education institution, in the areas of Life Sciences, Physical Sciences, Mathematics, Statistics and Informatics or Environmental Sciences;</li>
	<li>Hold a foreign higher education academic degree awarded following undergraduate studies, in Life Sciences, Physical Sciences, Mathematics, Statistics and Informatics or Environmental Sciences, organized in accordance with the principles of the Bologna Process by a State adhering to this Process;</li>
	<li>Hold a foreign higher academic degree in the areas of Life Sciences, Physical Sciences, Mathematics, Statistics and Informatics or Environmental Sciences that is recognized as meeting the objectives of the Bachelor’s degree by the ISA Scientific Council;</li>
	<li>SPresent an academic, scientific, or professional curriculum, attesting to the ability to carry out the study cycle which is recognized by the ISA Scientific Council.</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="pt-4 pb-3">Application dates</h3>

<p>The dates of the different application phases for 2023/2024 are as follows:</p>

<ul>
	<li><i>1st phase: 12 June to 14 July 2023</i></li>
	<li><i>2nd phase: 24 July to 18 August 2023</i></li>
	<li><i>3rd phase: 28 August to 10 September 2023</i></li>
</ul>

<h3 class="pt-4 pb-3">Application Submission</h3>

<p>Applications must be submitted online through ISA's Fenix ​​platform. Each applicant must create a new Fenix registration. For more information regarding the required documentation and submitting an application via Fenix, see the <a href="https://www.isa.ulisboa.pt/candidatos/candidaturas-2ciclo">following page</a>.</p>
